dct_description_sm: Published at Washington D.C. July 1906 ; O.H. Tittmann, Superintendent.
Depths shown by soundings; relief by hachures, contours, and spot heights.
Tides table, storm warning signs, Lights table, Light vessels, date of corrections by topic and source (Corps of Engineers, City Engineer of Providence).
Shows low water areas, various topographic features (vegetation, wetland), waterways, roads, buildings, railroads, lights, bells, buoys, small islands and rocks (named).
[Inset map]: Seekonk River : Continuation to Pawtucket
